    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-02T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-02T17:00:00-05:00" n="264"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d264">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">874.00/7–2845: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the United States Representative in Bulgaria</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Barnes</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-02T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 2, 1945—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>231. Dept transmitted substance Urtels 385 and 386<note n="17" xml:id="d264fn1">
                        <ref target="frus1945Berlinv02#pg_722">
                            <hi rend="italic">Conference of Berlin</hi> (<hi rend="italic"
                                >Potsdam</hi>), vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, pp. 722</ref> and
                            <ref target="frus1945Berlinv02#pg_724">724</ref>, respectively.</note>
                    to the Secretary of State at Potsdam for consideration.</p>
                <p>Meanwhile, suggestion urtel 395 July 28 has been communicated to OWI which
                    indicates it will include in its Voice of America Broadcasts in Bulgarian
                    substance Petkov’s letter with expressions of approval by press or other private
                    sources in this country of desire for democratic procedures evidenced
                    therein.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
